data.text:
Summer Walker's song 'SWV (feat. N01-NOAH)' delves into themes of intimacy, vulnerability, and the complexities of modern relationships. The title 'SWV' is a nod to the 90s R&B group Sisters With Voices, known for their hit 'Weak,' which is referenced in the lyrics. This connection sets the tone for the song, emphasizing the emotional and physical vulnerability that comes with deep romantic connections.

The lyrics paint a vivid picture of a passionate and somewhat tumultuous relationship. Walker sings about the thrill of new experiences and the intoxicating feeling of being desired. Lines like 'Rich sex, brand new / Tesla, I'm feelin' brand new' and 'I love it when you touchin' on me / It's like water' highlight the physical and emotional highs of the relationship. The repeated references to feeling 'weak in the knees' echo SWV's classic, underscoring the overwhelming nature of these emotions.

N01-NOAH's verse adds another layer to the narrative, exploring the darker, more obsessive side of love. His lyrics, 'Obsessed with the pussy causin' havoc' and 'Once I give you this dick, I'ma ruin your life up,' reveal a possessive and potentially destructive aspect of the relationship. This juxtaposition of pleasure and pain, love and obsession, creates a complex emotional landscape that many listeners can relate to. The song ultimately captures the duality of modern romance, where intense passion often comes with its own set of challenges and complications.
